In a dusky Krakow tea shoppe, the Magician waits impatiently for a meeting with his estranged protégée, the Knight of Swords. When Jude, the recluse Knight, arrives he learns a terrible truth; the Queen of Cups is dying. Reluctantly, he agrees to help the Magician find an urgent replacement within the Tarot – an ancient society bound by the principals of the seventy-eight card deck created to uphold the world’s complicated balance of opposing forces.  As Jude searches for a new Queen, the lives of a gypsy, a celibate Knight, and a supernatural spy, intertwine to determine the fate of our world....